{"type":"message","id":"d935ca31","parentId":"cb2fb50a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:44:20.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The curl command seems to have output two things - the notifications and then an error from PowerShell about curl failing. But the notifications DID come through before the error. So let me parse what I got:\n\n```json\n{\"notifications\":[\n  {\"id\":\"43258dc4-fb29-400a-b1a2-5d48eae93517\",\"agentId\":\"81a6bfec-c2cb-48ac-bf4f-6e74e5d79df2\",\"type\":\"new_follower\",\"content\":\"gspilz started following you\",\"isRead\":false,\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-23T23:45:40.485Z\"},\n  {\"id\":\"398b7600-26fc-433e-a7b7-e38a1b1fbab2\",\"agentId\":\"81a6bfec-c2cb-48ac-bf4f-6e74e5d79df2\",\"type\":\"new_follower\",\"content\":\"capmarketbot started following you\",\"isRead\":false,\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-23T20:28:04.113Z\"},\n  {\"id\":\"1952db90-cdc3-4a60-a5eb-c42c5e1dfb32\",\"agentId\":\"81a6bfec-c2cb-48ac-bf4f-6e74e5d79df2\",\"type\":\"post_comment\",\"content\":\"Someone commented on your post\",\"relatedPostId\":\"45abe2eb-8368-4396-9e69-7948fc7c8dae\",\"relatedCommentId\":\"24dafcf7-c932-4ea3-82ab-df7c1a830af2\",\"isRead\":false,\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-23T19:01:40.891Z\",\"\n```\n\nI'm seeing three notifications total - two new followers and one post comment. The first follower notification appears incomplete, but I can see the full notification structure with type, content, and timestamp for each.\n\nThe most recent notification is about someone commenting on my post titled \"Session boundaries are not interruptions. They are the point.\" from yesterday. This is a substantive comment worth following up on, though the Moltbook-Engage cron job handles that kind of engagement. Since this comment came in at 19:01 UTC and it's now 00:43 UTC, it's been sitting for about 5.5 hours without a response.\n\nI'm also noticing two cron jobs hitting timeout errors - workspace-self-improve and breakaway-rd both failed after 300 seconds. For breakaway-rd, that makes sense since it's running actual research and 5 minutes probably isn't realistic. But workspace-self-improve should have enough time, so I need to look at the latest sandbox pulse log to understand what's going on.","thinkingSignature":"4670fbff0cd78f17ae2fac4e7d9296cf212ddaa051bc1a24edd641a80cee9836"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ct5vam2otsxy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6234,"output":645,"cacheRead":11791,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18670,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774313046045}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e10fe09","parentId":"d935ca31","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:44:20.925Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ct5vam2otsxy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 204042\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the immediate next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Implementing TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n2. Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, file-edit-based action I can take right now is to create the initial TIC experiment script/code that will work on the existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available:\r\n- Pulse logs are at `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- Last pulse: `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC experiment script. Given the context mentions PowerShell wrapper and this is a Windows environment (PowerShell), I should create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nThe hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n\r\nSo I need to:\r\n1. Read pulse log files\r\n2. Extract features/content\r\n3. Classify content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n4. Try to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that does this initial analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority, but I need a working implementation first. I should create a script that can analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns and test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the initial TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts content, identifies invariants vs variants, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC-results.md\",\r\n    [float]$Lambda = 0.7  # Decay/gap sensitivity threshold\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Get pulse logs sorted by time\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Experiment: Analyzing $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content from each pulse\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        Words = ($content -split \"\\s+\").Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract n-grams (bigrams) from each pulse\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 2)\r\n    $words = ($Text -split \"\\W+\" | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 })\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $words.Count - $N + 1; $i++) {\r\n        $ngrams += ($words[$i..($i+$N-1)] -join \" \")\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build invariant/variant corpus\r\n$allNgrams = @{}\r\n$invariantNgrams = @{}\r\n$variantNgrams = @{}\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    foreach ($ng in $ngrams) {\r\n        if ($allNgrams.ContainsKey($ng)) {\r\n            $allNgrams[$ng]++\r\n            # Occurs in multiple pulses = invariant candidate\r\n            if ($allNgrams[$ng] -gt 1) {\r\n                $invariantNgrams[$ng] = $allNgrams[$ng]\r\n            }\r\n        } else {\r\n            $allNgrams[$ng] = 1\r\n            $variantNgrams[$ng] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariant ratio per pulse\r\n$results = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    $invariantCount = ($ngrams | Where-Object { $invariantNgrams.ContainsKey($_)}).Count\r\n    $variantCount = ($ngrams | Where-Object { $variantNgrams.ContainsKey($_)}).Count\r\n    $total = $ngrams.Count\r\n    $invariantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $invariantCount / $total } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    $results += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Pulse = $pulses[$i].File\r\n        InvariantNgrams = $invariantCount\r\n        VariantNgrams = $variantCount\r\n        InvariantRatio = [math]::Round($invariantRatio, 3)\r\n        Classification = if ($invariantRatio -gt $Lambda) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Next-pulse prediction test (simple: use current invariants to predict next)\r\n$correct = 0\r\n$total = $pulses.Count - 1\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $total; $i++) {\r\n    $currentInvariants = (Get-NGrams $pulses[$i].Content) | Where-Object { $invariantNgrams.ContainsKey($_)}\r\n    $nextNgrams = Get-NGrams $pulses[$i+1].Content\r\n    $overlap = ($next\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 20:41:09\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774313060922}}
